.pHive/*
# Legacy state/ — ignored completely. Harness sessions running the pre-rename
# Stop hook may briefly recreate state/interrupts/ files until the session
# restarts. Keeping state/ ignored prevents those files from polluting PRs.
state/
# meta-team state, team configs, and team-memories are plugin-level and should be tracked
!.pHive/meta-team/
!.pHive/meta-team/**
!.pHive/teams/
!.pHive/teams/**
!.pHive/team-memories/
!.pHive/team-memories/**
# Meta-improvement-system epic artifacts (planning + audit trail for maintainer tooling).
# The parent .pHive/epics/ and .pHive/episodes/ dirs must be un-ignored first —
# git will not recurse into an ignored directory even if a deeper negation exists.
!.pHive/epics/
!.pHive/episodes/
# Then re-ignore every child of those dirs except the meta-improvement-system subtree.
.pHive/epics/*
.pHive/episodes/*
!.pHive/epics/meta-improvement-system/
!.pHive/epics/meta-improvement-system/**
!.pHive/episodes/meta-improvement-system/
!.pHive/episodes/meta-improvement-system/**
agents/memories/
.claude/settings.local.json
.history/
.DS_Store
*.log
.claude/*.lock
